  "title": "Angel of the Sleepless City",
  "secondName": "Angel of the Sleepless City",
  "description": "A city where the lights seem to never go out, with countless buildings crammed together, and a sea of people as far as the eye can see. A place she doesn't know, customs she doesn't understand. Illuminated by flashing neon lights in every color imaginable, she felt more afraid than in the depths of the blackest, moonless night. That is, until she saw <i>it</i>.\nAn elegant form and a roaring engine resonating with the beat of her heart. Speed like nothing she ever experienced in her own world, the thrill of outrunning the wind. It was called \"a motorcycle,\" they told her. Once she got on, the city didn't seem so threatening anymore, and she found out just how addictive speed can be.",
